30:57.450 --> 30:59.350
Fuck you, man.

30:59.400 --> 31:03.600
Nah, I ain't leaving.
I'm not leaving my house.

31:03.650 --> 31:05.600
You're gonna have to kill me.

31:09.750 --> 31:12.650
I'm not leaving.

31:19.050 --> 31:22.750
[coughing]

32:23.000 --> 32:25.400
You're gonna need stitches.

32:25.450 --> 32:27.600
I can do it myself or I can refer you

32:27.650 --> 32:29.750
to a plastic surgeon in Austin.

32:31.950 --> 32:34.600
I was born here.

32:34.650 --> 32:36.950
I have a right to be here.

32:39.800 --> 32:43.250
When did he start burning
people's houses down?

32:43.300 --> 32:45.300
Tonight.

32:50.000 --> 32:52.800
You were who you said you were,

32:52.850 --> 32:54.750
you should have seen it coming.

32:54.800 --> 32:57.800
Yeah, well, you tell your husband

32:57.850 --> 33:00.100
I meant what I said.

33:02.100 --> 33:04.400
Ain't no avoiding it.

33:05.850 --> 33:07.850
Avoiding what?

33:20.850 --> 33:23.150
[high-pitched whining]

33:42.900 --> 33:44.900
[clock ticking]

33:46.950 --> 33:49.950
- [clock ticking louder]
- [high-pitched whining stops]

33:52.200 --> 33:54.550
[John snoring]

33:56.800 --> 33:59.300
[panting]

35:06.450 --> 35:08.650
[bird chirping]

35:27.600 --> 35:29.250
- What are you doing?
- Shh!

35:29.300 --> 35:30.850
[cricket chirps]

35:30.900 --> 35:34.100
Must be under something.

35:34.150 --> 35:36.550
- You're not gonna find it.
- No, I am gonna find it.

35:38.000 --> 35:39.800
Well, at least it got you out of bed.

35:39.850 --> 35:42.350
[chuckles] I got out of bed...

35:44.100 --> 35:48.000
so I could join y'all for church.

35:50.250 --> 35:52.000
Mm-hmm.

35:52.050 --> 35:53.500
Mm-hmm, what?

36:03.350 --> 36:05.600
- [cricket chirps]
- God damn it!

36:07.550 --> 36:09.850
<i>Michael: A reading from Thessalonians.</i>

36:09.900 --> 36:11.850
"Now we ask you, brothers,

36:11.900 --> 36:15.400
to give recognition to
those who labor among you

36:15.450 --> 36:17.800
and lead you in the
Lord and admonish you."

36:17.850 --> 36:19.150
Congregation: Yes. Yes.

36:19.200 --> 36:21.750
"And regard them very highly in love

36:21.800 --> 36:23.450
because of their work.

36:23.500 --> 36:25.300
Be at peace among yourselves."

36:25.350 --> 36:26.400
Yes. Yes.

36:26.450 --> 36:29.000
- "Comfort the discouraged."
- <i>Yes!</i>

36:29.050 --> 36:31.200
- "Help the weak."
- <i>Yes!</i>

36:31.250 --> 36:34.250
- "Be patient with everyone."
- <i>All right.</i>

36:38.400 --> 36:42.650
"See to it that no one repays
evil for evil to anyone.

36:42.700 --> 36:45.150
But always pursue what is good."

36:45.200 --> 36:47.950
- Yes!
- <i>That's right.</i>

36:49.950 --> 36:52.700
"For one another and for all."

36:52.750 --> 36:55.100
- <i>Yes!</i>
- <i>Hallelujah!</i>

36:55.150 --> 36:57.850
This is the word of the Lord.

36:57.900 --> 36:59.200
<i>Yes!</i>

36:59.250 --> 37:02.600
We are the 9,261.

37:02.650 --> 37:04.150
We are spared.

37:04.200 --> 37:06.150
All: We are spared.

37:06.200 --> 37:08.200
- And for that, we are grateful.
- All: Amen!

37:19.000 --> 37:21.650
Thank you, Michael.

37:21.700 --> 37:23.300
Just a reminder for y'all,

37:23.350 --> 37:26.050
I'm up in Austin this
week getting my surgery.

37:26.100 --> 37:28.550
So if you are so inclined,

37:28.600 --> 37:31.600
ask of the Lord for competent doctors.

37:31.650 --> 37:33.550
<i>Yes!</i>

37:33.600 --> 37:35.900
And a powerful anesthesia.

37:35.950 --> 37:37.900
[applause]

37:40.550 --> 37:42.750
So I'll miss a few sermons.

37:42.800 --> 37:46.000
But just like my hip, y'all
will get a great replacement.

37:46.050 --> 37:47.850
- All right.
- That's right.

37:47.900 --> 37:50.950
Met him doing some missionary
work down in Brazil.

37:51.000 --> 37:54.150
- He don't know our style...
- <i>That's all right.</i>

37:54.200 --> 37:55.500
...but he knows the Good Book.

37:55.550 --> 37:57.400
<i>Amen, amen.</i>

37:57.450 --> 37:59.100
Better than most.

37:59.150 --> 38:01.700
Certainly better than me.

38:01.750 --> 38:05.350
My friend Matt Jamison.

38:05.400 --> 38:07.550
[applause]

38:14.500 --> 38:16.000
Thank you, Reverend Massey.

38:16.050 --> 38:17.700
I'm so grateful for your kindness

38:17.750 --> 38:19.700
and for letting me be here.

38:21.450 --> 38:23.800
I haven't had the pleasure
of meeting most of you yet.

38:23.850 --> 38:29.450
We've... My wife Mary and I
have only been here for a month or so.

38:30.500 --> 38:33.350
Well, I'm a man of faith.

38:33.400 --> 38:36.100
Amen!

38:36.150 --> 38:39.350
But when I heard about this place,

38:39.400 --> 38:40.800
when I heard about what happened here,

38:40.850 --> 38:43.650
I'd be lying if I told
you I understood it.

38:43.700 --> 38:45.450
<i>Yes, yes.</i>

38:45.500 --> 38:47.200
But I understand it now.

38:47.250 --> 38:49.150
[applause]

38:49.200 --> 38:50.800
Because you've shared your home with me,

38:50.850 --> 38:52.800
I want to share with you
what has happened to us,

38:52.850 --> 38:54.750
to Mary,

38:54.800 --> 38:58.150
who I was told by countless
doctors would never recover.

38:58.200 --> 39:00.000
Thank you, Matt.

39:00.050 --> 39:02.750
We all know what a truly
special place we've got here.

39:02.800 --> 39:04.350
<i>Yes!</i>

39:04.400 --> 39:06.750
Massey: And I know I speak
for everyone here when I say,

39:06.800 --> 39:08.050
welcome, brother.

39:08.100 --> 39:10.150
- Welcome!
- Welcome, sister.

39:11.600 --> 39:13.800
- Praise Jesus.
- Amen!

39:21.200 --> 39:24.600
Now let us bow our heads for a
reading from the Gospel of Luke.

39:26.700 --> 39:28.900
- So nice to have you.
- Thank you.

39:33.850 --> 39:35.850
- Matt: Hi.
- Massey: Thank you, sir. Thank you.

39:37.400 --> 39:40.600
John. So nice to see
your face in there today.

39:40.650 --> 39:42.250
What you talking about,
now? Come on, now, Calvin.

39:42.300 --> 39:44.500
You're gonna make the new reverend
here think I never come to church.

39:44.550 --> 39:46.450
[both laugh]

39:46.500 --> 39:48.850
- John Murphy.
- John, nice to meet you.

39:48.900 --> 39:50.900
Matt Jamison, my wife Mary.

39:50.950 --> 39:53.450
A pleasure, Mary.

39:53.500 --> 39:55.850
Welcome to Jarden.

39:55.900 --> 39:57.850
Now, where you two in from?

39:57.900 --> 40:00.600
Mapleton, New York. It's
just outside the city.

40:00.650 --> 40:03.050
- New York City.
- Ah, figured.

40:03.100 --> 40:05.050
- [laughs]
- Yeah.

40:05.100 --> 40:07.700
- So what were you gonna say up there?
- I'm sorry?

40:07.750 --> 40:09.450
Well, right before
Calvin here cut you off.

40:09.500 --> 40:13.700
Seemed like you were about to
share something about your wife.

40:13.750 --> 40:15.450
Oh. [chuckles]

40:15.500 --> 40:17.450
I was just gonna say that I felt a burden

40:17.500 --> 40:20.050
lift off of us when we came to your town.

40:20.100 --> 40:23.000
For the first time in a
long time, we feel safe.

40:24.900 --> 40:28.000
Well, there's no place
in the world safer.

40:29.950 --> 40:32.000
- Y'all take care.
- Thank you.

40:32.050 --> 40:33.550
- Mm-hmm.
- [music playing]

40:36.100 --> 40:39.150
- [music continues]
- [chattering]

40:39.200 --> 40:42.450
Sorry, I asked for the
bacon on a separate plate.

40:42.500 --> 40:45.250
You got it. I'll bring
that right back for you.

40:45.300 --> 40:47.050
Every time.

40:47.100 --> 40:50.050
Well, it wouldn't be every time
if they'd listen, sweetheart.

40:53.300 --> 40:57.350
"See to it that no one repays
evil for evil to anyone."

40:59.300 --> 41:01.950
Any particular reason
you picked that one?

41:03.300 --> 41:06.400
I didn't pick it.
Readings are predetermined.

41:08.800 --> 41:11.700
What is a Thessalonian anyway?

41:11.750 --> 41:13.350
Someone from Thessalonia.

41:13.400 --> 41:14.800
From Arkansas, right?

41:14.850 --> 41:16.300
[all laugh]

41:17.700 --> 41:19.450
Bacon and eggs separated.

41:19.500 --> 41:21.400
Appreciate it.

41:21.450 --> 41:23.750
[goat bleats]

41:30.700 --> 41:32.100
Jerry, come on.

41:32.150 --> 41:34.950
[goat bleats]

41:37.900 --> 41:39.350
Jerry, please.
Do you have to...

41:41.500 --> 41:43.400
[goat thuds]

41:45.850 --> 41:47.150
[clicks]

41:48.650 --> 41:50.200
Sorry, folks.

42:00.250 --> 42:02.150
Enrique.

42:02.200 --> 42:04.800
[music playing on TV]

42:04.850 --> 42:06.950
<i>Narrator: "Perfect Strangers"
star Mark Linn-Baker</i>

42:07.000 --> 42:09.750
<i>departed on October 14, 2012,</i>

42:09.800 --> 42:12.850
<i>but "Hard 10" tracked him
down to this sleepy village</i>

42:12.900 --> 42:15.000
<i>in the Chihuahua province of Mexico.</i>

42:15.050 --> 42:16.850
<i>Woman: We know you didn't depart, Mark.</i>

42:16.900 --> 42:18.850
<i>Why'd you fake your departure?</i>

42:18.900 --> 42:21.250
<i>No comprende. No comprende.</i>

42:21.300 --> 42:22.700
<i>Woman: We know it's you, Mark.</i>

42:22.750 --> 42:24.750
<i>Mark: No Mark. No Mark esta.</i>

42:24.800 --> 42:27.000
<i>Woman: Mark, tell us why
you did it. Tell us why.</i>

42:27.050 --> 42:29.000
<i>Damn! Damn it!</i>

42:31.750 --> 42:35.600
<i>Narrator #2 on TV: They're gone,
but so much of them is still here.</i>

42:35.650 --> 42:38.350
[music playing]

42:38.400 --> 42:42.350
<i>You've tried to move on,
tried to live a normal life,</i>

42:42.400 --> 42:46.200
<i>but cannot let go because
you haven't known how.</i>

42:46.250 --> 42:48.200
[continues indistinctly]

43:15.300 --> 43:17.200
[spoon rattling]

43:29.750 --> 43:31.350
- Michael: Hey.
- [gasps]

43:31.400 --> 43:34.650
Uh...

43:34.700 --> 43:38.600
my spoon got stuck in
the garbage disposal.

43:49.500 --> 43:51.400
I'm going for a ride.

43:55.500 --> 43:57.750
Other people feed him, you know.

43:57.800 --> 43:59.800
He likes Mom's cooking.

44:01.800 --> 44:04.450
Back by 10:00.

44:04.500 --> 44:06.700
Be safe.

44:12.300 --> 44:14.400
[door opens]

44:16.000 --> 44:17.650
- <i>[cricket chirps]</i>
- [door closes]

44:35.650 --> 44:38.450
- You mail the letter?
- Uh-huh.

44:42.700 --> 44:44.750
Good night.

44:52.400 --> 44:54.300
<i>Man: Get off me! Hey,
we just missed the bus.</i>

44:54.350 --> 44:55.950
<i>Officer: Sure, you did. Head down, sir.</i>

44:56.000 --> 44:57.850
- Ma'am, calm down.
- You can't keep us out.

44:57.900 --> 45:00.050
- Calm down, ma'am.
- Fuck you, man. This is fucking America.

45:00.100 --> 45:01.400
- [Taser crackles]
- Ah!

45:01.450 --> 45:02.900
<i>Man: You can't keep people out, man.</i>

45:02.950 --> 45:06.000
<i>You're not so special. Fuck
your fucking wristbands!</i>

45:39.050 --> 45:41.900
[TV playing]

45:54.450 --> 45:55.650
Hello.

45:55.700 --> 45:57.800
Hi.

45:57.850 --> 45:59.700
You want to pray?

46:03.300 --> 46:05.200
Okay.

46:37.850 --> 46:39.400
[vehicle approaches]

47:01.850 --> 47:04.800
[music playing]

47:33.350 --> 47:35.600
- What's that?
- It's a pie.

47:35.650 --> 47:38.250
- Where'd it come from?
- It was on the porch.

47:38.300 --> 47:39.650
Is it for your birthday?

47:39.700 --> 47:42.150
- I don't know.
- There wasn't a note?

47:42.200 --> 47:44.400
- Just a pie.
- Hmm.

47:44.450 --> 47:47.200
- What kind is it?
- Apple, I think.

47:47.250 --> 47:49.750
- Looks homemade.
- Mm-hmm.

47:51.200 --> 47:53.300
You think someone's trying to poison you?

47:57.500 --> 47:59.100
[laughs] Look at your face.

47:59.150 --> 48:01.150
[laughs]

48:03.050 --> 48:06.350
You know someone just
moved in the Dunbar house.

48:06.400 --> 48:08.400
- A family.
- Just now?

48:08.450 --> 48:10.250
Mm-hmm. Seem nice.

48:14.000 --> 48:17.150
I think we ought to invite
them over for dinner tonight.

48:18.550 --> 48:20.600
You're gonna work on your birthday?

48:22.250 --> 48:24.200
Just being neighborly.

48:39.250 --> 48:41.150
- Hi.
- Hey.

48:41.200 --> 48:44.950
Saw you moving in. I'm John Murphy.

48:45.000 --> 48:47.050
We're right next door.

48:47.100 --> 48:49.050
Here. Welcome.

48:49.100 --> 48:53.050
Oh, thanks. That's so nice. I'm Nora.

48:53.100 --> 48:55.200
Well, I see you got your hands full.

48:55.250 --> 48:57.300
No problem. I got her. Did
you bake this yourself, John?

48:57.350 --> 48:59.500
No, ma'am, I did not.

48:59.550 --> 49:00.850
And who's this?

49:00.900 --> 49:04.000
This is Lily. Say hello
to Mr. Murphy, Lily.

49:04.050 --> 49:05.850
- [coos]
- Hey, Lily.

49:05.900 --> 49:07.400
[banging]

49:07.450 --> 49:09.050
Is everything all right in there?

49:09.100 --> 49:11.300
Fine, we're just moving
in. You know, chaos.

49:11.350 --> 49:13.150
Of course. Well, I'll leave you to it.

49:13.200 --> 49:15.250
Just wanted to invite
you all over tonight.

49:15.300 --> 49:17.350
Having a little barbecue for my birthday.

49:17.400 --> 49:20.600
That's so... We don't want
to crash your birthday.

49:20.650 --> 49:24.050
No, no pressure. Just drop by if you can.

49:24.100 --> 49:26.750
Thank you.

49:26.800 --> 49:28.600
- Bye-bye.
- Bye, Lily.

49:34.000 --> 49:36.000
You ask them if they eat meat?

49:36.050 --> 49:37.950
I told them it was a barbecue.

49:38.000 --> 49:40.500
If they don't eat meat, that would
have been the time to tell me.

49:40.550 --> 49:42.600
Violet wants to know
when she can pick me up.

49:42.650 --> 49:46.150
Well, you tell Violet
that you will text her

49:46.200 --> 49:48.500
as soon as I authorize you to do so.

49:48.550 --> 49:50.450
Nora: Hello!

49:50.500 --> 49:52.450
Sorry, we rang the doorbell,
but nobody answered.

49:52.500 --> 49:54.600
We're back here. Come on down.

49:57.350 --> 50:00.450
It's Kevin. You're John, right?

50:00.500 --> 50:02.600
Right. Right. This is Erika.

50:02.650 --> 50:04.500
- Hi. Hi.
- Hi, Erika. How are you? Nice to meet you.

50:04.550 --> 50:06.200
Evie, Michael, introduce yourselves.

50:06.250 --> 50:07.800
- How you doing?
- Michael.

50:07.850 --> 50:10.950
- I'm Nora.
- Nice to meet you.

50:12.400 --> 50:15.500
- Hi.
- Hey.

50:15.550 --> 50:18.100
- So are we early, or...
- No, right on time.

50:18.150 --> 50:20.700
Oh, I thought this was a birthday party.

50:20.750 --> 50:23.650
It is. We don't have any friends.

50:23.700 --> 50:25.300
[laughing]

50:25.350 --> 50:27.000
- Erika: Who is this?
- Nora: This is Lily.

50:27.050 --> 50:28.650
Erika: Well, hello, Lily.

50:28.700 --> 50:31.250
- [laughter, chattering]
- <i>♪ I don't need sunglasses ♪</i>

50:31.300 --> 50:35.950
♪ Ain't no sun without you, baby... ♪

50:36.000 --> 50:38.700
- She's adorable.
- Thank you.

50:38.750 --> 50:41.000
Is she adopted or did
your mom fuck a black dude?

50:41.050 --> 50:42.150
Evie!

50:43.000 --> 50:44.950
[laughs]

50:45.100 --> 50:47.100
[laughs]

50:49.600 --> 50:51.000
You don't need that anymore.

50:51.050 --> 50:52.950
You guys bought the house, right?

50:53.000 --> 50:55.400
Yeah, but they said that we should
leave them on for a couple weeks

50:55.450 --> 50:57.750
so the park rangers don't
bother us or something.

50:58.900 --> 51:01.050
Your daughter is good with a baby.

51:01.100 --> 51:02.550
That's got to be nice.

51:02.600 --> 51:04.550
Oh, she's not mine. She's Kevin's.

51:04.600 --> 51:06.400
Oh, well, she's pretty.

51:06.450 --> 51:08.600
So is he.

51:08.650 --> 51:11.150
His secret is moisturizing.

51:11.200 --> 51:13.200
[laughs]

51:13.250 --> 51:15.050
So you have family around here?

51:15.100 --> 51:18.000
- Sorry?
- In Jarden.

51:18.050 --> 51:20.600
I figured someone must have
tipped you off about the house.

51:20.650 --> 51:22.450
Real estate moves
pretty quick around here.

51:22.500 --> 51:25.200
Oh, no, we were just in the
right place at the right time.

51:25.250 --> 51:27.550
I have a brother, Matt Jamison.

51:27.600 --> 51:29.250
He and his wife came out
here a couple months ago.

51:29.300 --> 51:31.450
He's helping out in the
Baptist church. You know him?

51:31.500 --> 51:35.200
I just met him yesterday. Small world.

51:41.300 --> 51:42.900
Kevin: Cake looks good.

51:42.950 --> 51:46.650
Well, she works the grill, I bake.

51:46.700 --> 51:49.250
[laughs]

51:49.300 --> 51:51.400
Now, what happened to your head?

51:51.450 --> 51:53.200
I fell.

51:56.600 --> 51:58.650
Can I... can I put
these in the fridge?

51:58.700 --> 52:00.550
Absolutely.

52:07.200 --> 52:08.650
You want one?

52:08.700 --> 52:11.100
Uh, nah. I don't drink.

52:11.150 --> 52:13.100
But help yourself.

52:14.800 --> 52:16.350
Okay.

52:29.700 --> 52:31.600
What?

52:34.150 --> 52:36.250
What? What?

52:36.300 --> 52:38.050
Oh, what were you looking at?

52:38.100 --> 52:41.800
I was just looking at your
couch in the other room.

52:41.850 --> 52:43.800
We had one just like it.

52:43.850 --> 52:45.850
[can pops]

52:49.500 --> 52:50.700
[laughter]

52:50.750 --> 52:54.750
So I step on the carpet
and I feel this squish.

52:54.800 --> 52:58.000
I walk around the corner
and trickling down the steps

52:58.050 --> 53:00.750
like a fancy fountain is water,

53:00.800 --> 53:02.800
- but in my house.
- [laughing]

53:02.850 --> 53:04.500
So I'm walking up these steps.

53:04.550 --> 53:07.400
And you know when you
feel like it's a bad idea,

53:07.450 --> 53:10.100
but you do it anyway?

53:10.150 --> 53:13.350
I open the bathroom door
and this wave comes out.

53:13.400 --> 53:15.650
A little one, but a wave.

53:15.700 --> 53:18.250
And this one is standing in the bathtub

53:18.300 --> 53:20.650
with her arms out like Moses

53:20.700 --> 53:23.500
and this one's up on the sink

53:23.550 --> 53:25.700
trying his hardest not to get wet.

53:25.750 --> 53:27.950
And he just looks at me
with this serious face

53:28.000 --> 53:31.700
and goes, "Evie wanted to
know what would happen."

53:31.750 --> 53:33.750
[laughing]

53:33.800 --> 53:36.000
Gets funnier every time, Mama.

53:36.050 --> 53:37.850
- Nora: How old were they?
- Five.

53:37.900 --> 53:40.700
And they're lucky they made it to six.

53:40.750 --> 53:42.450
That must have been fun to come home to.

53:42.500 --> 53:44.550
Well, I was in prison.

53:44.600 --> 53:46.350
Oh, yeah? Well, how
long were you there for?

53:46.400 --> 53:49.300
Six years, 119 days.

53:49.350 --> 53:51.150
[chuckles]

53:52.400 --> 53:53.800
They think you're kidding.

53:53.850 --> 53:56.850
Oh, sorry, no. I really was.

53:56.900 --> 53:59.000
Travis County Unit.

54:02.150 --> 54:04.000
Go ahead.

54:04.050 --> 54:06.650
- Go ahead and ask.
- What?

54:06.700 --> 54:09.950
What I did. It's what
everybody wants to know.

54:10.000 --> 54:12.700
- Oh, that's none of our business.
- What'd you do?

54:12.750 --> 54:14.900
Huh.

